cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the capacity of a network where users send information to a remote destination through relay nodes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of cloud radio access networks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also establishes a single-letter characterization of the capacity region, which is a topic related to coding theory (cs.CC) and information theory. Finally, the paper discusses the role of time-sharing, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
